    "### 1.2 Original Dataset Overview"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2ba89c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This project focuses on the SQuAD 2.0 (Stanford Question Answering Dataset), a widely used benchmark for extractive question answering based on Wikipedia articles. Each example consists of a context paragraph and a question, and the goal is to determine whether the question can be answered using the provided context and, if so, to extract the corresponding answer span directly from the text.\n",
    "\n",
    "A key feature of SQuAD 2.0 is the inclusion of unanswerable questions, where the context does not contain sufficient information to produce a valid answer. As a result, models must not only identify relevant spans but also learn to detect when no answer is supported by the context. This significantly increases the complexity of the task compared to earlier extractive QA benchmarks.\n",
    "\n",
    "The objective of this project is to perform an exploratory data analysis (EDA) to better understand the dataset’s structure, linguistic patterns, and statistical properties, providing a solid foundation for the development and evaluation of machine learning models."
   ]
  },
