   "source": [
    "The results show that nouns (NOUN) and proper nouns (PROPN) dominate both questions and contexts, highlighting a strong focus on entities and factual content. Questions tend to have a slightly higher proportion of auxiliary verbs (AUX) and pronouns (PRON), reflecting their interrogative structure. Contexts, instead, contain more adjectives (ADJ) and coordinating conjunctions (CCONJ), indicating richer and more descriptive text.  "
