    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ba3bb1f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The results show a high frequency of relations such as \"det\", \"prep\", \"pobj\", \"nsubj\", and \"dobj\", which are typical of structured interrogative sentences. These patterns reflect common question forms like \"What year did...\", \"Who wrote...\", or \"Where was...\", where subjects, objects, and prepositional phrases play a central role.  \n",
    "The presence of relations like \"attr\" and \"aux\" further supports the standard construction of factual questions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "84448837",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This next plot compares the distribution of syntactic dependency relations between answerable and unanswerable questions, to verify whether differences in question structure are associated with answerability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 858,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1400x650 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Separate dependency relations by label to compare syntactic structure\n",
    "dep_ans   = Counter()\n",
    "dep_unans = Counter()\n",
    "\n",
    "for doc, y in zip(docs_dep, sample_q_df['y']):\n",
    "    # Exclude punctuation and ROOT — focus on meaningful grammatical relations\n",
    "    deps = [tok.dep_ for tok in doc if tok.dep_ not in ('punct', 'ROOT')]\n",
    "    if y == 1:\n",
    "        dep_ans.update(deps)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        dep_unans.update(deps)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Normalize counts to percentages for fair comparison between groups\n",
    "total_ans   = sum(dep_ans.values())\n",
    "total_unans = sum(dep_unans.values())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take union of top-k relations from both groups\n",
    "top_k = 12\n",
    "all_deps = list(\n",
    "    {k for k, _ in dep_ans.most_common(top_k)} |\n",
    "    {k for k, _ in dep_unans.most_common(top_k)}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Order relations by average percentage across the two groups\n",
    "all_deps = sorted(\n",
    "    all_deps,\n",
    "    key=lambda d: (\n",
    "        dep_ans.get(d, 0) / total_ans * 100 +\n",
    "        dep_unans.get(d, 0) / total_unans * 100\n",
    "    ) / 2,\n",
    "    reverse=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "perc_ans   = [dep_ans.get(d, 0)   / total_ans   * 100 for d in all_deps]\n",
    "perc_unans = [dep_unans.get(d, 0) / total_unans * 100 for d in all_deps]\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.arange(len(all_deps))\n",
    "width = 0.38\n",
    "\n",
    "# ---------- Figure ----------\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 6.5))\n",
    "fig.patch.set_facecolor('#F8FAFC')\n",
    "ax.set_facecolor('white')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bars\n",
    "ax.bar(\n",
    "    x - width/2,\n",
    "    perc_ans,\n",
    "    width,\n",
    "    label='Answerable',\n",
    "    color='#2563EB',\n",
    "    alpha=0.88,\n",
    "    edgecolor='white',\n",
    "    linewidth=0.8\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.bar(\n",
    "    x + width/2,\n",
    "    perc_unans,\n",
    "    width,\n",
    "    label='Unanswerable',\n",
    "    color='#F59E0B',\n",
    "    alpha=0.88,\n",
    "    edgecolor='white',\n",
    "    linewidth=0.8\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Axes and labels\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(x)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(\n",
    "    all_deps,\n",
    "    rotation=35,\n",
    "    ha='right',\n",
    "    fontsize=11,\n",
    "    color='#0F172A'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title(\n",
    "    'Dependency Relations by Label',\n",
    "    fontsize=14,\n",
    "    fontweight='bold',\n",
    "    color='#0F172A',\n",
    "    pad=12\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\n",
    "    'Percentage (%)',\n",
    "    fontsize=11,\n",
    "    color='#475569'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=10.5, colors='#475569')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Style\n",
    "ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['left'].set_color('#E2E8F0')\n",
    "ax.spines['bottom'].set_color('#E2E8F0')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.yaxis.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.7, color='#E2E8F0')\n",
    "ax.set_axisbelow(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend(\n",
    "    frameon=True,\n",
    "    facecolor='white',\n",
    "    edgecolor='#E2E8F0',\n",
    "    framealpha=1,\n",
    "    fontsize=11\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c44a813b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The comparison shows that the overall distribution of dependency relations is very similar across the two groups, suggesting that both answerable and unanswerable questions follow comparable syntactic patterns.  \n",
    "However, small differences can be observed: for example, answerable questions tend to have slightly higher proportions of relations like \"det\", \"prep\", and \"pobj\", while unanswerable ones show marginally higher values for relations such as \"compound\", \"dobj\", and \"aux\".  \n",
    "These differences are limited, indicating that syntax alone is not a strong discriminative feature for answerability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d05986b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As part of the dependency parsing analysis, we analyze the POS of the ROOT token, which represents the syntactic head of the sentence. In a dependency tree, the ROOT is the central node from which all other words depend, so analyzing its POS helps to understand the core structure of questions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 859,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x550 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Count the POS tag of the ROOT token — the main predicate of each question\n",
    "root_pos = Counter()\n",
    "\n",
    "for doc in docs_dep:\n",
    "    for tok in doc:\n",
    "        if tok.dep_ == 'ROOT':\n",
    "            root_pos[tok.pos_] += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "# ---------- Data ----------\n",
    "items = root_pos.most_common()\n",
    "\n",
    "labels_r = [k for k, _ in items][::-1]\n",
    "vals_r   = [v for _, v in items][::-1]\n",
    "total_r  = sum(vals_r)\n",
    "\n",
    "# ---------- Figure ----------\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5.5))\n",
    "fig.patch.set_facecolor('#F8FAFC')\n",
    "ax.set_facecolor('white')\n",
    "\n",
    "bars = ax.barh(\n",
    "    labels_r,\n",
    "    vals_r,\n",
    "    color='#0891B2',\n",
    "    edgecolor='white',\n",
    "    linewidth=0.7\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Percentage labels\n",
    "for bar, v in zip(bars, vals_r):\n",
    "    ax.text(\n",
    "        bar.get_width() + bar.get_width()*0.02,\n",
    "        bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,\n",
    "        f'{v/total_r:.1%}',\n",
    "        va='center',\n",
    "        fontsize=10.5,\n",
    "        color='#0F172A'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "# Titles\n",
    "ax.set_title(\n",
    "    'POS of ROOT Token in Questions',\n",
    "    fontsize=14,\n",
    "    fontweight='bold',\n",
    "    color='#0F172A',\n",
    "    pad=12\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\n",
    "    'Count',\n",
    "    fontsize=11,\n",
    "    color='#475569'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, max(vals_r) * 1.22)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Style\n",
    "ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)\n",
    "ax.spines['left'].set_color('#E2E8F0')\n",
    "ax.spines['bottom'].set_color('#E2E8F0')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.xaxis.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.7, color='#E2E8F0')\n",
    "ax.set_axisbelow(True)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=10.5, colors='#475569')\n",
    "ax.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=11, colors='#0F172A')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5edcc39d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The results show that the vast majority of questions have a verb (VERB) or auxiliary verb (AUX) as the root, accounting for more than 90% of cases. This reflects the typical structure of interrogative sentences, which are usually centered around an action or a predicate (e.g., \"What did...\", \"Who is...\", \"When was...\").  \n",
    "Other POS categories appear only marginally, confirming that questions are strongly verb-driven."
   ]
  },
